criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Aged 5-65 years;
2. Expected survival beyond 12 weeks;
3. Patients with B-cell hematologic malignancies, and consistent with allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation standards;
4. Creatinine <2.5mg/dl;
5. ALT /AST<3 normal value;
6. Bilirubin < 2.0 mg/dl;
7. Karnofsky score >50;
8. Patients without severe liver, kidney, heart disease;
9. Voluntary participation in the clinical trials.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Patients in pregnancy or breast-feeding period; Planning pregnancy within 6 months;
2. HIV or active TB infected;
3. Active hepatitis B or hepatitis C infection;
4. Feasibility assessment during screening demonstrates <10% transduction of target lymphocytes, or insufficient expansion (<5-fold) in response to CD3/CD28 costimulation;
5. Patients with abnormal vital signs or could not cooperate with inspectors;
6. History of mental disorders;
7. Highly allergic constitution or severe allergies, especially allergic to IL-2;
8. Systemic infection or serious infections should be local anti-infection treatment;
9. With heart, lung, brain, kidney and other important organ dysfunction;
10. Presence of severe autoimmune disease;
11. Other situations we think improper for the research.
